speech.p:
asked the Minister of Agriculture (1) whether he is aware that the proposed purchase of a sugar-refining undertaking in Liverpool will have the effect of creating a monopoly of sugar-refining in that district; and what action he proposes to take, in view of Section 8 of the Sugar Industry (Reorganisation) Act, 1936;

(2) whether, in consenting to agreements for the refining of sugar, made under Section 8 of the Sugar Industry (Reorganisation) Act, 1936, he has regard to the importance of preventing the


creation of a monopoly applying to refining in any particular district?
